    "description": "Ubiquitous AI Corporation develops and sells embedded software products primarily in Japan and internationally. The company offers various products, including Ubiquitous Securus, an anti-tamper security solution for embedded devices; Ubiquitous TPM Security, a security software solution for trusted platform module; Edge Trust, a solution for enabling secure IoT services; Ubiquitous Network Framework, a TCP/IP stack-based middleware; Ubiquitous DTCP, a link protection middleware; and Ubiquitous HDCP, a software development kit optimized for HDCP implementation. It also provides Ubiquitous WPA/WPS/Wi-Fi Direct, a software development kit for developing the functionalities necessary for wireless LAN clients to acquire the Wi-Fi certification logo; Ubiquitous QuickBoot, a fast boot solution for Linux and Android; Ubiquitous DeviceSQL, a data management software for embedded systems; and Ubiquitous USB host platform. In addition, the company offers Ubiquitous Miracast Solution, a wireless environment software for remote display connection; Ubiquitous ECHONET Lite, a middleware software; Ubiquitous Wi-SMART, a middleware software; Ubiquitous TLS/SSL, a security protocol; TOPPERS-Pro Series, an RTOS solution package; and Ubiquitous DLNA SDK, a middleware software. Further, it imports and sells software products; and provides technical support and customize development services. The company offers software analysis and development efficiency tools, security products, and support services related to its offerings. Its services include software development, distribution, and sales of data content licenses, as well as the design and production of various software, primarily contracted software for thin-film applications. The company was formerly known as Ubiquitous Corporation and changed its name to Ubiquitous AI Corporation in July 2018 operations. Ubiquitous AI Corporation was incorporated in 2001 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
